&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advanced Nurse Practitioner Trauma &amp; Orthopaedics, Band 8a&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fixed-Term/Secondment: 12 months due to funding&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder is an experienced practitioner who, acting within his/her professional boundaries, oversees admissions and on-going pathway care for all orthopaedic trauma patients admitted to the West Middlesex University Hospital. This includes providing care for the presenting patient, from initial history taking, clinical assessment, diagnosis, treatment and evaluation of care. There will be particular focus on peri-operative care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will work autonomously as a senior professional within Trust and NMC policies, protocols and guidelines. They will demonstrate safe clinical decision-making, high levels of critical thinking and holistic practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a practitioner they will also be working within the national framework and adhering to statutory and regulatory requirements inclusive of maintaining a professional portfolio of practice and competence. The registered nurse working at this level will have had a higher level of education and training at master’s degree and have significant roles within each of the four pillars of:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced clinical practice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitation of education and learning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evidence research and development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role may require the post-holder to cover evening/weekend and on-call duties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nuno Cunha, Lead Nurse Surgery&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;nuno.cunha@chelwest.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07899773090&lt;/p&gt;
